Text.Value: Chk. A kith'rak's time is precious. Waste it at your peril.
A fortune in gold, vouched for by our queen herself.
Does this look like an infirmary?
I need a description of the weapon you seek.
Only return if you have the weapon. I will not tolerate insubordination.
Leave.
You are forbidden to leave. Report to the Inquisitor at once. Deliver the Prism.
What does this weapon look like?
You would invoke rank? On a kith'rak? Pathetic, vin'iisk.
Forgive me - I misspoke. There is no traitor.
I have found the weapon we seek.
You are mistaken. The hunt for the weapon is the Inquisitor's folly, not mine - but it is not your place to question orders.
You are not familiar to me, ra'stil. Do you bring news of the weapon?
Information. Chk. If it's not about the weapon we seek, I don't care.
You ask me? I would relish nothing more than burning the ghaik threat from this rock.
You are well informed. My crèche discovered the same.
Then learn to tame your tongue. I will ask one last time: have you brought the weapon?
I have what you're looking for.
Arrogance - a typical symptom of the istik condition. But an arrogant tracker is a tracker nonetheless.

EditorData.NodeContext: superior, rude, insulting humans for being human

Text.Value: I have proof of the illithid invasion - it might help your Inquisitor to rethink his priorities.
The very same said to hold the weapon we seek.
If you speak truth, the Inquisitor will reward you greatly. If you lie...
Hshar'lak among us?
Your doctor.
Then squander my time no more. Go. Now.
But I cannot imagine this is what our queen wants.
Chk - vague allegations and undue demands. A poor introduction for an unproven vin'iisk.
Chk - vague allegations and undue demands. A poor introduction for an unproven istik.
I presume you are not stupid enough to return empty-handed. So give me the weapon - now.
I believe I have found the weapon we seek.
Don't tell her anything.
Don't tell her anything.
Time is finite. As is my patience. Go.
The Jhe'stil Kith'rak?
The Inquisition never explain themselves.
No. NO!
No. NO!
Do not try to leave or it will be your death!

EditorData.AnimationTags: [ChristianD] Captain is being pushed by the energy blast that was released by the artifact.
EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: The artefact's glow pulses into a shockwave of energy, blasting the captain off her feet and propelling the artefact back to the player. The player picks it up.
EditorData.SFXTags: [RS] Energy blast as the artifact rips itself from the cpatain's psyonic grip and flies back to the player
EditorData.VFXTags: [RS] Energy blast as the artifact rips itself from the cpatain's psyonic grip and flies back to the player, trail of energy behind the box as it flies

EditorData.AnimationTags: [ChristianD] Captain uses her telekinesis to pull the artifact away from Player's hand
EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: The captain moves her hand, psionic energy gathering. She closes her fist and pulls towards her. The artefact is pulled to the captain. She holds it suspended in the air with her psionics. It begins to glow
EditorData.SFXTags: [RS] Psyonic enegery as the captain uses her telekinesis to pull the artifact to her - lead in
EditorData.VFXTags: [RS] Psyonic enegery as the captain uses her telekinesis to pull the artifact to her -  lead in

Text.Value: What is so important about this weapon?
I was told to seek your infirmary.
Attack.
Produce the artefact.
*You sense Shadowheart's worry. This 'weapon' sounds like the artefact you carry.*

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Shadowheart looks at the player, deeply worried.

Text.Value: And yet your face betrays you. You found it, didn't you?
I have important information.
Finish your business here, and leave.
The Inquisitor? On what grounds?
Then our ghustil will study your corpse.
...Well. Inquisitor W'wargaz will ensure you do not bother me again.

EditorData.InternalNodeContext: BarrierDeactivated state flag on here temporarily until new scripting is submitted.

Text.Value: Not yet.
I was granted entry by your sentries. They told me to seek the Inquisitor.
It appears you have been chosen, vin'iisk. How lucky you are.
It appears you have been chosen, istik. You are lucky it is not for me to question why.
You manipulate it when I cannot?
I seek audience with your Inquisitor. There's a traitor among you.
Whom would you accuse?
What does this weapon look like?
I know nothing about the weapon.
Weapon? I seek aid. We should be fighting the ghaik incursion.
I have business to attend to. Return with the weapon, or do not return at all.
We know infected flock to Moonrise Towers. I reported the gathering masses back to Tu'narath.
Maybe I can help you find the weapon.
Produce the artefact.
Meanwhile, illithid sickness spreads right in front of us.
You have returned. Any news of the weapon?
I will not.
Chk - a strong accusation from the mouth of a vin'iisk. The very same said to hold the weapon we seek.
Chk - a strong accusation from the mouth of an istik. The very same said to hold the weapon we seek.
I think I have what you're looking for.
An istik. In my crèche. You are one of the mercenaries sent to bring the weapon?

EditorData.NodeContext: Isitk should be spat here, she is disgusted by you

Text.Value: I sincerely hope you know what you're doing...

EditorData.NodeContext: A whispered, worried exclamation from Shadowheart, she's terrified

Text.Value: I am no mercenary, but I am a good tracker. Describe the weapon - I can help you.
I do not. My apologies.
No.
Tsk'va! Trickery, heresy, how did you -

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: The captain scrambles to her feet after being knocked down by a blast from the artefact
EditorData.NodeContext: she gets into an angry rant and then rights herself, reallising it's not worth it

Text.Value: Still, perhaps you've heard of it. Tell me, does this sound familiar?
Then why, ra'stil, do you waste my time?
Then stop wasting my time, istik.
Take the weapon yourself, then. Seek the ch'r'ai below.
Go, seek the Inquisitor below. And take the cursed thing with you.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: The captain begins to walk towards the barrier device.

Text.Value: I'm to report to your infirmary for investigation.
Inquisitor W'wargaz has the Queen's ear, so we have no choice but to follow him in this folly.
Leave.
I don't know anything about it.
What was that look? You know something. Do you have it?
What is so important about this weapon?
*You realise she seeks the artefact you carry.*

EditorData.NodeContext: A whispered, worried exclamation from Shadowheart, she's terrified

Text.Value: Kith'rak Voss.
Yes - there it is. Exactly as described. The inquisition will finally come to an end.

EditorData.AnimationTags: [ChristianD] Captain in idle examining the suspended artifact above her palm.
EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Therezzyn studies the artefact suspended before her.
EditorData.SFXTags: [RS] Psyonic energy pulses as it holds the artifact up
EditorData.VFXTags: [RS] Psyonic energy pulses as it holds the artifact up

Text.Value: I do not know - this hunt is the Inquisitor's folly, not mine.
If the Inquisition seeks this weapon, it must be vital. Tell me of it.
He speaks the truth, kith'rak.
She speaks the truth, kith'rak.
They speak the truth, kith'rak.
It is small. Angular. Metal. Adorned with tir'su script. Stolen by 'True Soul' heretics.

EditorData.InternalNodeContext: flag this for knowng what the artefact looks like

Text.Value: Using my room as a thoroughfare is an indignity. Disturbing me is an insult. Begone.
We have all the proof we need and it has not moved his resolve.

EditorData.NodeContext: with fatigue - she has tried this argument many times with the inquisitor and failed

Text.Value: The ghustil?
You are here to - no. You are here to die.
You are one of the mercenaries we engaged, are you not?
You must have impressed him, to be let out so readily.

EditorData.InternalNodeContext: 'him' is the Inquisitor. Captain doesn't know he's dead.
EditorData.NodeContext: with a hint of jealousy - she's not managed to impress the inquisitor yet

Text.Value: What's the reward again?
Where is the infirmary, then?
*She seeks the artefact you carry - the artefact now nestled in your pocket, that doesn't want to be relinquished.*
I'll gladly see you try. Htak'a!
The istik is with me, honoured kith'rak.
Can you give me a description of the weapon you seek?
The ghustil's office is past the dormitories. Go, vin'iisk.
Our healer's office is past the dormitories. Go, before I send you as a corpse.
Ch'mar zal'a Vlaakith! Give it to me.

EditorData.NodeContext: cheh-MAR ZAL-ah VLAH-kith - means 'Vlaakith's will above all' - used in the way that we may say 'Praise the Lord!'

Text.Value: You have orders. See them done.

EditorData.InternalNodeContext: She doesn't like that you've got more important things to do than she does.

Text.Value: Sure I have a weapon. Want to see your blood on it?
Of course. I will be back on the search immediately.
No? Then I will take it from your corpse.
So noted. But my question goes unanswered. Do you bring the weapon?
Here it is.
Your sentries thought I could be of use to the Inquisitor.
What I know can only be heard by the Inquisitor. You must let me pass.
There's a mind flayer invasion in progress. Why is that not your priority?
Honoured kith'rak. May Vlaakith show us truth.
I told you, they will stop at nothing to reclaim it.
I told you, they will stop at nothing to reclaim it.
To value a mere weapon so much is pure vanity. You should worry more about your warriors.
By command of the Inquisition, you are ordered to join in our search. Return with the weapon, or do not return at all.
That is only for your Inquisitor to know. Take me to him.
I've not found it yet - but I'm close. I just need more time.
In response, they sent an Inquisitor. Instead of ordering an assault, we were told to join in this mad hunt for an ancient relic.
Perhaps. Tell me, ra'stil, does this sound familiar?
Tell me, istik, does this sound familiar?
Not exactly. I'm here to loot the place.

Synopsis:
Captain Therezzyn of Creche Yllek interrogates the player about the missing githyanki "weapon". We should learn:
1. The githyanki's missing weapon and our artefact are THE SAME
2. the githyanki were planning to attack moonrise towers
